I have a timer in my game which simply shows minute and second.

On android backend when I exit game using home button at 00:10 and open game after 10 seconds my timer continues from 00:11 and that's OK. But When I do the same thing on robovm backend, timer continues from 00:20.

I compared `com.badlogic.gdx.backends.android.AndroidGraphics.onDrawFrame` and `com.badlogic.gdx.backends.iosrobovm.IOSGraphics.draw` methods where `deltaTime` is calculated.

In terms of pseudo code, for android backend it is like

```
calculateDeltaTime();
if (paused)
    return;
renderGame();
```

But for robovm backend it is like

```
if (paused)
    return;
calculateDeltaTime();
renderGame();
```

Now it is clear why my timer counts the time that is passed while game was paused (:

I have a stage in libgdx app. If I implement resize like this:

public void resize (int width, int height) {
    stage.setViewport(800, 480, true);
    stage.getCamera().translate(-stage.getGutterWidth(), -stage.getGutterHeight(), 0);
}
It works well. On iPad I'm getting black bars on top and bottom, so it works just like expected. The problem is I have some objects outside stage and they're drawing on black bars. So the next method from docs should do the work:

public void resize (int width, int height) {
    Vector2 size = Scaling.fit.apply(800, 480, width, height);
    int viewportX = (int)(width - size.x) / 2;
    int viewportY = (int)(height - size.y) / 2;
    int viewportWidth = (int)size.x;
    int viewportHeight = (int)size.y;
    Gdx.gl.glViewport(viewportX, viewportY, viewportWidth, viewportHeight);
    stage.setViewport(800, 480, true, viewportX, viewportY, viewportWidth, viewportHeight);
}

But it doesn't. The stage is drawn on the whole screen, so everything is stretched. But it looks like stage touches works only in right place and only "visual" stage is force to fill screen.

But If I run this on desktop and set the same dimension as iPad I'm getting black bars and everything goes well.

My logs from iPad and desktop:

[info] dims: 1024, 768
[info] viewport: 0, 76, 1024, 614

dims: 1024, 768
viewport: 0, 76, 1024, 614

Please fix it :)

I have come across an issue when trying to play a music object with the exception: "GdxRuntimeException: Unabe to allocate audio buffers". 

I have downloaded the latest nightly builds, and the issue still happens. This is running on the desktop with Windows 7 (64 bit).

Basically, I am disposing of the music and sound resources when I switch from Area 1 to Area 2 in my game and then loading new resources for Area 2 (using the AssetManager). The crash happens when I switch back to Area 1 and reload the previously unloaded sounds and music.

I modified the Drop sample project as it is easier to demonstrate the issue I have. I understand the example is not what you would normally do, but it is the easiest way to show how the problem manifests itself. 

1) If I run the following code with all Music objects, no problems.
2) If I run the following code with all Sound objects, no problems.
3) If I run the following code with the Gdx.audio.newSound uncommented (commenting out the other portion instead), works without any problems.

I have used newSound() as a workaround for the Sound objects, but this isn't optimal. I have looked at examples, so it is not entirely obvious to me if I am doing something wrong.

4) If I run the following code code with how it is, a mix of one Music file and a bunch of sound files using AssetManager, it crashes when it tries to play the music object with the following exception:

180             rainMusic.play();       

Exception in thread "LWJGL Application" com.badlogic.gdx.utils.GdxRuntimeException: Unabe to allocate audio buffers.
    at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.openal.OpenALMusic.play(OpenALMusic.java:76)
    at com.badlogic.drop.GameScreen.render(GameScreen.java:180)
    at com.badlogic.gdx.Game.render(Game.java:46)
    at com.badlogic.drop.Drop.render(Drop.java:20)
    at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication.mainLoop(LwjglApplication.java:207)
    at com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication$1.run(LwjglApplication.java:114)

Code:

```
package com.badlogic.drop;

import java.util.Iterator;

import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Input.Keys;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.Texture;
import com.badlogic.gdx.assets.AssetManager;
import com.badlogic.gdx.audio.Sound;
import com.badlogic.gdx.audio.Music;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.OrthographicCamera;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.g2d.SpriteBatch;
import com.badlogic.gdx.math.Rectangle;
import com.badlogic.gdx.graphics.GL10;
import com.badlogic.gdx.math.Vector3;
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array;
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.TimeUtils;
import com.badlogic.gdx.math.MathUtils;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Screen;

public class GameScreen implements Screen {
    final Drop game;

    Texture dropImage;
    Texture bucketImage;
    Sound dropSound;

    Music rainMusic;

    Sound drop1;
    Sound drop2;    
    Sound drop3;
    Sound drop4;    
    Sound drop5;    
    Sound drop6;    
    Sound drop7;    
    Sound drop8;    
    Sound drop9;    
    Sound drop10;

    Boolean toggle = true;

    OrthographicCamera camera;
    SpriteBatch batch;

    Rectangle bucket;

    Array<Rectangle> raindrops;
    long lastDropTime;

    public static AssetManager _AssetManager;

    public GameScreen(final Drop gam) {
        this.game = gam;

        //load the images for the droplet and the bucket, 64x64 pixels each
        dropImage = new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("droplet.png"));
        bucketImage = new Texture(Gdx.files.internal("bucket.png"));

        _AssetManager = new AssetManager();

        //load the drop sound effect and the rain background "music"
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop.wav").path(), Sound.class);
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy.wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (2).wav").path(), Sound.class);
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (3).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (4).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (5).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (6).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (7).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (8).wav").path(), Sound.class);  
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (9).wav").path(), Sound.class);

        //load asset
        _AssetManager.load(Gdx.files.internal("rain.mp3").path(), Music.class);

        _AssetManager.finishLoading();


        camera = new OrthographicCamera();
        camera.setToOrtho(false, 800, 480);

        batch = new SpriteBatch();
        bucket = new Rectangle();
        bucket.x = (800 / 2) - (64 / 2);
        bucket.y = 20;
        bucket.width = 64;
        bucket.height = 64;

        raindrops = new Array<Rectangle>();
        spawnRaindrop();
    }

    @Override
    public void dispose() {
        dropImage.dispose();
        bucketImage.dispose();
        rainMusic.dispose();
        batch.dispose();
    }

    @Override
    public void render(float delta) {       
        Gdx.gl.glClearColor(0, 0, 0.2f, 1);
        Gdx.gl.glClear(GL10.GL_COLOR_BUFFER_BIT);

        camera.update();

        batch.setProjectionMatrix(camera.combined);
        batch.begin();
        batch.draw(bucketImage, bucket.x, bucket.y);
        for(Rectangle raindrop: raindrops){
            batch.draw(dropImage, raindrop.x, raindrop.y);
        }
        batch.end();

        if(Gdx.input.isTouched())
        {
            Vector3 touchPos = new Vector3();
            touchPos.set(Gdx.input.getX(), Gdx.input.getY(),0);
            camera.unproject(touchPos);
            bucket.x = touchPos.x - (64/2);
        }

        if(Gdx.input.isKeyPressed(Keys.LEFT)){
            bucket.x  -= 200 * Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime();
        }

        if(Gdx.input.isKeyPressed(Keys.RIGHT)){
            bucket.x += 200 * Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime();
        }

        if( bucket.x < 0 ){
            bucket.x = 0;
        }

        if( bucket.x > (800 - 64) ){
            bucket.x = 800 - 64;
        }

        if(TimeUtils.nanoTime() - lastDropTime > 1000000000){
            spawnRaindrop();
        }

        Iterator<Rectangle> iter = raindrops.iterator();
        while(iter.hasNext()){
            Rectangle raindrop = iter.next();
            raindrop.y -= 200 * Gdx.graphics.getDeltaTime();

            if( raindrop.y + 64 < 0){
                iter.remove();
            }

            if( raindrop.overlaps(bucket)){

                if( toggle ){
                    toggle = false;

                    rainMusic = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("rain.mp3").path());
                    drop1 =  _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop.wav").path());
                    drop2 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy.wav").path());    
                    drop3 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (2).wav").path());
                    drop4 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (3).wav").path());    
                    drop5 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (4).wav").path());    
                    drop6 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (5).wav").path());    
                    drop7 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (6).wav").path());    
                    drop8 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (7).wav").path());    
                    drop9 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (8).wav").path());    
                    drop10 = _AssetManager.get(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (9).wav").path());   

                    /*
                    drop1 =  Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop.wav"));
                    drop2 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy.wav"));  
                    drop3 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (2).wav"));
                    drop4 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (3).wav"));  
                    drop5 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (4).wav"));  
                    drop6 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (5).wav"));  
                    drop7 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (6).wav"));  
                    drop8 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (7).wav"));  
                    drop9 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (8).wav"));  
                    drop10 = Gdx.audio.newSound(Gdx.files.internal("drop - Copy (9).wav"));
                    */      

                    rainMusic.play();       
                    rainMusic.setLooping(true);

                    drop1.play();
                    drop2.play();   
                    drop3.play();
                    drop4.play();   
                    drop5.play();   
                    drop6.play();   
                    drop7.play();   
                    drop8.play();   
                    drop9.play();   
                    drop10.play();  
                }
                else
                {
                    toggle = true;
                    rainMusic.dispose();                

                    drop1.dispose();
                    drop2.dispose();    
                    drop3.dispose();
                    drop4.dispose();    
                    drop5.dispose();    
                    drop6.dispose();    
                    drop7.dispose();    
                    drop8.dispose();    
                    drop9.dispose();    
                    drop10.dispose();       
                }

                iter.remove();
            }
        }

    }

    @Override
    public void resize(int width, int height) {
    }

    @Override
    public void pause() {
    }

    @Override
    public void resume() {
    }

    private void spawnRaindrop(){
        Rectangle raindrop = new Rectangle();
        raindrop.x = MathUtils.random(0, 800-64);
        raindrop.y = 480;
        raindrop.height = 64;
        raindrop.width = 64;
        raindrops.add(raindrop);
        lastDropTime = TimeUtils.nanoTime();
    }

    @Override
    public void show() {
        // TODO Auto-generated method stub
        //rainMusic.play();
    }

    @Override
    public void hide() {
        // TODO Auto-generated method stub

    }
}

